         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/12/1884 ¶  ¶ Let me offer, dear Louise, my best thanks for the beautiful Christmas Card, sent by you with such affectionate inscription; and let me also offer my felicitation to you at the approach...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.12.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Louise Wehl</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M100a, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/12/1884</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me offer, dear Louise, my best thanks for the beautiful Christmas Card, sent by you with such affectionate inscription; and let me also offer my felicitation to you at the approach of a new year. May it be to you then one of great happiness. I should like to see you nearer to your dear mother, and trust that an opportunity will arise, to see that wish fulfilled. It is very honorable of you, that you pushed your own way in the world; and every one must give you praise for that.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We had here a Conference of the Sydney- and Melbourne-geographic Society, so that much extra inroad was made into my time for two weeks, and the departmental work came much into arrear. I have therefore worked through out the holidays, and have even now no time to write you a long letter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day I revised a lot of Examination-papers of the Sydney-University, of which I am a medical Examiner.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Mama writes,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that you sent her such a beautiful photographic card of you; can you spare me one also?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ettie sent me hers also, which shows her to be a most beautiful and intelligent young Lady.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henrietta Wehl, M's niece.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M acknowledged receiving the photograph that Louise sent in response to his request in M to L. Wehl, 10<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>January 1885.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Neither that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>image<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nor Ettie's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been identified at MEL, but see M to J. Haast, 29 July 1862 (in this edition as 62-07-29b) and notes thereto.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
